condition.narrative: Financing Agreement: Compensation for Land Acquisition | Description: TANAP shall, in relation to resettlements under the Project,pay all expenditures and any other related payments referenced under the RAPs. | Frequency: Continuous [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: Grievance Redress and Appeals Mechanism | Description: TANAP shall (a) maintain a grievance redress mechanismfor TANAP; and (b) establish within 30 days of the date of the first signed Loan Agreement and maintain four independent AppealsGrievance Redress Committees, for addressing complaints not resolved by TANAP's grievance mechanism related to the implementationof the ESIA Package. | Frequency: Continuous [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: Impact Evaluation of RAP Implementation | Description: TANAP shall no later than one calendar year after thecarrying out the RAPs, conduct and furnish to the Bank impact evaluation studies on the outcome of resettlement activities carriedout by TANAP. | Due Date: 31-Dec-2020 [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: Implementation of the ESIA Package | Description: TANAP shall ensure that the Project (including all workperformed by contractors) is carried out in accordance with the provisions of the environmental and safeguards documents thatconstitute the Environmental and Social Impact (ESIA) Package, including the Resettlement Action Plans (RAPs). | Frequency:Continuous [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: Independent ESIA Monitoring and Reporting | Description: TANAP shall maintain independent third partymonitoring firms, with staffing and terms of reference satisfactory to the Bank, to independently monitor the Project'simplementation progress and compliance with terms of the ESIA Package, and to prepare and submit quarterly ESIA monitoring reportsand semi-annual external monitoring reports of the RAPs to TANAP and the Bank. Environmental monitoring firm was appointed in 2015.The social monitoring firm will be appointed within 45 days of the date of the first signed Loan Agreements. | Frequency: Quarterly[also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: Information to the Bank on Significant Events | Description :TANAP shall within five days after itsoccurrence, notify the Bank of any significant environmental, occupational health and safety related event; and within 30 daysprovide the Bank with a summary report that includes a description of such significant event, and the measures that TANAP is takingor plans to take to address the event and to prevent any future similar events. | Frequency: Continuous [also applies toIBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: Occupational Health and Safety | Description: TANAP shall implement its Working Hours Action Plan inaccordance with the compliance schedule set forth in the Plan. | Frequency: Continuous [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: Progress Reporting | Description: TANAP shall monitor and evaluate the progress of the Project and prepare andsubmit to the Bank monthly Project Reports. | Frequency: Monthly [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: TANAP's Capacity to Implement the Project | Description The Borrowers shall cause TANAP, through theSubsidiary Agreements, to maintain capacity satisfactory to the Bank for carrying out its responsibilities under the Project. |Frequency: Continuous [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: TANAP's Consulting Services Support | Description: TANAP shall maintain, during the execution and untilcompletion of the Project, a contractor for engineering services. | Frequency :CONTINUOUS [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: TANAP's Contractors' Compliance with the World Bank's Anti-Corruption Guidelines | Description: TANAP shallensure all contractors financed by the Loans have expressly agreed to comply with the provisions of the World Bank'sAnti-Corruption Guidelines (ACGs), including the Bank's right to audit. (Financing will only be extended to contracts assessed bythe Bank to be eligible, and for which the Project Implementing Entity has received of the respective contractors'€™ writtennotification of their acceptance of the ACGs.). | Frequency: Continuous [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: TANAP's Integrated Project Management Structure | Description: TANAP shall maintain, during the execution anduntil completion of the Project, an integrated Project management structure consisting of TANAP and external consulting staff. |Frequency: Continuous [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: The Borrowers' Capacity to Oversee Project Implementation | Description: The Borrowers shall maintain, eitheritself or through an agent or affiliate acting on its behalf, a dedicated technical team to oversee the implementation of theProject and to liaise with TANAP. | Frequency: Continuous [also applies to IBRD-86810]

Financing Agreement: Transfer of TANAP Shares from SGC to SOCAR Turkey | Description: SGC shall promptly furnish to the Bankevidence reasonably requested by the Bank of its intended sale of seven percent of its shares in TANAP to SOCAR Turkey Enerji A.S.The resulting reduction of SGC'€™s shares in TANAP shall result in an equivalent reduction in the percentage of the Projectexpenditures to be financed from the SGC Loan proceeds. | Due Date :30-Sep-2017 [indicative]
